    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-23T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-23T14:00:00-05:00" n="346"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/385</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-23T20:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 23, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 23, 7.04 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10235. War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1"
                        >Sheldon</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 645. Foreign Office and <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WM1"
                        >Wallenberg</persName> do not think that the form of adhesion proposed in my
                    560, Embassy’s 10003, May 11, 5 p.m. <pb facs="0404" n="1238" xml:id="pg_1238"/>
                    and modified by your 511, Department’s 7834, May 20, 6 p.m., is sufficient, as
                    it will not provide for undertaking in the tonnage agreement concerning
                    bunkering and licensing of vessels. Would you agree to following clause being
                    added to the approved form of adhesion: “and the War Trade Board during the
                    currency of the above-mentioned agreement [will issue licenses] for the
                    bunkering of Swedish vessels in accordance with the terms of the tonnage
                    agreement and will adhere to the terms of such tonnage agreement which is a part
                    of the general agreement”?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Laughlin</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
